    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Modernist chair designed for Knoll International in 1952 by Harry Bertoia. The basic form of the chair is constructed from wire rods welded together. There are many variations in upholstery and finish.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000014861/Fehrman, Popular Interior Design (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000096613/Museum of Modern Art (MoMA), New York [online] (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>哈瑞‧貝托亞(Harry Bertoia)於西元1952年，為諾爾家具公司(Knoll International)所設計富有現代主義風格的椅子。椅體的基本構造由多條金屬桿鍛接組成，座椅襯墊和塗漆有多種款式變化。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Moderner Stuhl, der 1952 von Harry Bertoia für Knoll International entworfen wurde. Die Grundform des Stuhles wird aus zusammengeschweißten Drahtstäben hergestellt. Es existieren zahlreiche Varianten in Polsterung und Ausführung.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
